@*
@page "/girlswhoconnect/childsafetystandards"

<PageTitle>Girls Who Connect</PageTitle>

<GirlsWhoWalkHeader />
<!-- ===== HERO SECTION ===== -->
<section class="hero-section">
    <div class="hero-inner">
        <div class="hero-content">
            <div class="hero-image">
                <img src="/images/Girls Who Connect/Child.png" alt="
" />
            </div>

            <div class="hero-text">
                <h1>Child Safety Standards</h1>
                <p>
                    The Girls Who Connect app is designed for adults aged 18+. We do not knowingly
                    allow minors to create accounts or use the platform. This page explains how the
                    app meets the 11 Child Safe Standards through its features, policies, and moderation
                    practices.

                    <br /><br />

                    Effective Date: 12th August 2025
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<style>
    :root {
        --brand: #efb2c4;
    }

    html, body {
        overflow-x: clip;
    }

    .hero-section {
        position: relative;
        display: flex;
        justify-content: center;
        align-items: flex-start;
        width: 200%;
        left: 50%;
        transform: translateX(-50%);
        height: 150%;
        padding-top: calc((var(--hero-extra, 20%) / 2));
        padding-bottom: 100px;
        box-sizing: border-box;
        z-index: 1;
        overflow: hidden;
        background: var(--brand);
        margin-top: -6rem; /* ⬅️ moves the whole section upward */
    }


    /* Content wrapper stays centered horizontally */
    .hero-inner {
        padding-top: 5vh;
        margin: 0 auto;
        width: min(var(--page-max, 1100px), 50%);
    }



    /* Wave as BACKGROUND (behind content) */
    .hero-section::after {
        content: "";
        position: absolute;
        left: 0;
        right: 0;
        bottom: -20px; /* moves it 20px lower */
        height: 140px; /* wave height */
        pointer-events: none;
        z-index: 0; /* behind content */
        background-repeat: no-repeat;
        background-position: bottom center;
        background-size: 100% 100%;
        transform: translateY(-16px); /* ✅ lifts wave upward slightly */
        /* White wave so it fades into the white section below */
        background-image: url('data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg viewBox="0 0 1440 120" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" preserveAspectRatio="none"><path d="M0,32 C240,96 480,0 720,48 C960,96 1200,32 1440,64 L1440,120 L0,120 Z" fill="%23ffffff"/></svg>');
    }

    .hero-content {
        position: relative;
        z-index: 1;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: space-between;
        gap: 2rem;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        flex-direction: row; /* ✅ ensures side-by-side on desktop */
    }

    .hero-text {
        flex: 1 1 400px;
        color: #111;
        text-align: left;
        order: 1; /* ✅ text first */
    }

        .hero-text h1 {
            font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 3vw, 2.4rem);
            font-weight: 800;
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
            color: #111;
        }

        .hero-text p {
            font-size: 1.05rem;
            line-height: 1.5;
            color: #333;
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
            max-width: 500px;
        }

    .hero-image {
        flex: 1 1 400px;
        display: flex;
        justify-content: center;
        align-items: center;
        order: 2; /* ✅ image second (on the right) */
    }

        .hero-image img {
            display: block;
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 500px;
            height: auto;
            object-fit: contain;
            border-radius: 16px;
            transition: transform 0.3s ease;
        }

    /* ===== Responsive ===== */
    @@media (max-width: 800px) {

        .hero-section {
            flex-direction: column;
            text-align: center;
            padding-bottom: 95px; /* keep good spacing */
        }

            .hero-section::after {
                height: 120px;
                transform: translateY(-12px); /* less lift for small screens */
            }

        .hero-image img {
            max-width: 340px;
            order: 1;
        }

        .hero-text {
            text-align: center;
            order: 2;
        }
    }

    @@media (max-width: 400px) {
        .hero-content {
            margin-top: 2rem; /* adjust as needed */
        }
    }
</style>


<section class="info-section" aria-labelledby="info-title">
    <div class="info-inner">
        <h2 id="info-title">Design Choices</h2>
        <div class="info-content">
            <div class="info-text">
                <p>
                    Key design choices for safety: The app does not support one-to-one (DM) messaging;
                    conversations occur only in location-based group chats. Users cannot “block”
                    others; instead, moderators review reports and can remove content and accounts.
                    The app uses a rough location (e.g., area/city) chosen by the user to join a
                    location chat; it does not share precise GPS coordinates.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="info-inner">
        <h2 id="info-title">Standard 1: Culturally Safe Environment</h2>
        <div class="info-content">
            <div class="info-text">
                <p>
                    We promote an inclusive app experience that respects diverse cultural
                    identities, including Aboriginal children and young people. Discrimination,
                    racism, or culturally unsafe behaviour is prohibited and removed upon
                    report/review.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="info-inner">
        <h2 id="info-title">Standard 2: Leadership, Governance and Culture</h2>
        <div class="info-content">
            <div class="info-text">
                <p>
                    Child safety is embedded in our policies and moderation. We maintain a zero-tolerance
                    stance on grooming, exploitation, or sexualised content involving minors. Any account
                    found to be involved in such behaviour is permanently banned from the app. Credible
                    reports are acted on swiftly, and serious matters are escalated to relevant law
                    enforcement agencies for investigation.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="info-inner">
        <h2 id="info-title">Standard 3: Empowerment and Participation</h2>
        <div class="info-content">
            <div class="info-text">
                <p>
                    If a minor is detected or reported on the app, we act immediately to protect their
                    safety by removing their account, securely storing any relevant evidence (such as
                    profile details, chat messages, or images) for investigation purposes, and notifying
                    appropriate law enforcement agencies when warranted - for example, in cases involving
                    suspected grooming, exploitation, or sexualised content.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Currently, concerns can be reported by emailing
                    <strong>matt@kenyondevlabs.com</strong>. Additional in-app reporting options are
                    being developed to make it even easier for users to report unsafe behaviour directly.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="info-inner">
        <h2 id="info-title">Standard 4: Families and Communities</h2>
        <div class="info-content">
            <div class="info-text">
                <p>
                    We publish our safety rules and procedures on our website so anyone can read them.
                    You don’t have to be a registered app user to send us a concern - parents or other
                    community members can email us directly.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="info-inner">
        <h2 id="info-title">Standard 5: Equity and Diverse Needs</h2>
        <div class="info-content">
            <div class="info-text">
                <p>
                    Safety processes are applied fairly to all users regardless of background or identity.
                    We aim for accessible language and straightforward reporting mechanisms.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="info-inner">
        <h2 id="info-title">Standard 6: Suitability of People</h2>
        <div class="info-content">
            <div class="info-text">
                <p>
                    Admin and developer accounts with moderation powers are vetted before elevated access
                    is granted. Breaches of safety expectations result in immediate removal of access.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="info-inner">
        <h2 id="info-title">Standard 7: Child-Focused Complaints Process</h2>
        <div class="info-content">
            <div class="info-text">
                <p>
                    At present, users can report concerns by emailing
                    <strong>matt@kenyondevlabs.com</strong>. In-app reporting features for messages in
                    location-based group chats are being developed to make it easier to flag unsafe
                    behaviour directly. Reports involving suspected minors are prioritised within 24
                    hours, and urgent cases are escalated to law enforcement without delay. We keep
                    reasonable records of all reports and the actions taken in response.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="info-inner">
        <h2 id="info-title">Standard 8: Knowledge, Skills, and Training</h2>
        <div class="info-content">
            <div class="info-text">
                <p>
                    Admins in the app are users who help run location-based groups. They do not have
                    moderation powers over user accounts or content beyond managing their group activities.
                    All moderation and child safety actions related to the app are handled by the
                    development team.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="info-inner">
        <h2 id="info-title">Standard 9: Safe Online Environments</h2>
        <div class="info-content">
            <div class="info-text">
                <ul>
                    <li>No 1:1 messaging; only location-based group chats to reduce private solicitation risk.</li>
                    <li>Rough location only - users select an area or city to join its chat; no GPS sharing.</li>
                    <li>Moderation and reporting: currently via email; in-app reporting for group chat messages coming soon.</li>
                    <li>Developers can remove content or accounts as needed.</li>
                    <li>Explicit or sexualised content involving minors is strictly banned and reported.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="info-inner">
        <h2 id="info-title">Standard 10: Review and Improvement</h2>
        <div class="info-content">
            <div class="info-text">
                <p>
                    We review child safety policies at least annually and after any material incident.
                    We monitor safety metrics (e.g., report volume, response times) to improve processes.
                    In-app reporting features will be implemented soon after rollout to provide users with
                    a faster and more direct way to flag safety concerns.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="info-inner">
        <h2 id="info-title">Standard 11: Policies and Procedures</h2>
        <div class="info-content">
            <div class="info-text">
                <p>
                    This page forms part of our public safety documentation. Internal guidelines cover
                    report handling, evidence preservation, account actions, and cooperation with
                    authorities.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="info-inner">
        <h2 id="info-title">Reporting Concerns</h2>
        <div class="info-content">
            <div class="info-text">
                <p>
                    If you believe a child or young person may be at risk on the Girls Who Connect app,
                    please report immediately:
                </p>
                <p><strong>Email:</strong> matt@kenyondevlabs.com</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="info-inner">
        <h2 id="info-title">Legal Compliance</h2>
        <div class="info-content">
            <div class="info-text">
                <p>
                    We comply with relevant UK child protection laws, including the
                    <strong>Children Act 1989 & 2004</strong>, the <strong>Sexual Offences Act 2003</strong>,
                    and the <strong>Protection of Children Act 1978</strong>. We cooperate fully with lawful
                    requests from authorities and report serious offences without delay.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<style>
    /* ===== Info Section (Text + Image) ===== */
    .info-section {
        color: #111;
        padding: 0;
        box-sizing: border-box;
        background: #fff;
        margin-top: -20px;
    }

    .info-inner {
        width: min(var(--page-max, 1100px), 100%);
        margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .info-section h2 {
        text-align: left;
        font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 3vw, 2rem);
        font-weight: 800;
        margin: 1rem 0 0.75rem 0;
    }

    .info-content {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: space-between;
        gap: 2rem;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
    }

    .info-text {
        flex: 1 1 480px;
        color: #333;
        line-height: 1.6;
        font-size: 1.05rem;
        min-width: 0;
        text-align: left;
    }

        .info-text p {
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
        }

    .info-image {
        flex: 1 1 420px;
        display: flex;
        justify-content: flex-start;
        min-width: 0;
    }

        .info-image img {
            display: block;
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 480px;
            height: auto;
            border-radius: var(--radius, 16px);
            box-shadow: 0 10px 24px rgba(0,0,0,.1);
        }

    /* ===== Responsive Stack ===== */
    @@media (max-width: 800px) {
        .info-content {
            flex-direction: column-reverse;
            align-items: flex-start;
            justify-content: flex-start;
            text-align: left;
            gap: 0rem;
            margin-top: 0;
        }

        .info-text,
        .info-image {
            flex: 0 0 auto;
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 480px;
        }

            .info-image img {
                max-width: 360px;
            }

        .info-section h2 {
            text-align: left;
        }
    }
</style>
*@